The PEFTI Film Institute has opened its Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board-accredited Computer-Based Testing centre in the Bodija area of Ibadan, Oyo State. According to a statement sent to Saturday Beats by the institute, the state-of-the-art CBT centre would provide a wide range of services, including JAMB registration, correction of data, printing of admission letters, printing of original JAMB results, NYSC registration, and a professional testing centre. The organisation is also said to be fully equipped with effective computer systems, fast Internet services, conducive environment, uninterrupted power supply, and other facilities. The Managing Director of PEFTI, Abiola Adenuga, noted that centre was one of the goals of the organisation. She said, “The opening of the CBT centre in Ibadan is one of the many goals we have been working on as part of our innovative expansion towards satisfying the needs of more members of society. All COVID-19 precautions have been put in place to ensure the facility is 100 per cent safe, and comfortable, as our many services are utilised by private individuals and corporate organisations.”